        <updateDate>2017-04-20T20:38:23Z</updateDate>
        <text>
          <![CDATA[ <p><b>Ensuring Diverse Leadership at the Federal Reserve Act of 2016</b></p> <p>This bill amends the Federal Reserve Act to require that in making the appointment of a president, a Federal Reserve Bank must interview at least one individual reflective of gender diversity and one reflective of racial or ethnic diversity.</p> <p>The bill amends numerous banking-, finance-, and trade-related Acts to make references to officials (including those to the Chairman of the Board of Governors of the Federal Reserve System) gender-neutral. </p>]]>
        </text>
      </summary>
